Before finalizing any documentation, verify:

- [ ] Document has a clear, descriptive title
- [ ] Opening paragraph explains the document's purpose
- [ ] Headings follow the hierarchy rules
- [ ] Code blocks have language specified
- [ ] All internal links use relative paths
- [ ] Related documentation section is present
- [ ] No duplicate information from other docs
- [ ] Language is clear and concise
- [ ] Steps are numbered and actionable
- [ ] Examples are minimal but complete
